generalfeedback.text: Recall that a maximum point is the point at the top of each crest and a minimum point is the point at the bottom of a dip. So in this case max = {@max@} and min ={@min@}. The amplitude is the distance between a maximum (or a minimum) and the principal axis, so we calculate: \[ A = \frac{max-min}{2} = \frac{{@max@}-{@min@}}{2} = {@ta3@}. \]
